```

## Error Handling

The framework provides a comprehensive exception hierarchy:

- `ScrapingError`: Base exception
  - `DownloadError`: HTTP request failures
    - `DownloadTimeout`: Request timeout
    - `HTTPError`: Non-2xx status codes
    - `ConnectionError`: Connection failures
  - `ParseError`: Content parsing failures
    - `SelectorError`: Invalid CSS/XPath selectors
    - `ContentError`: Malformed content
  - `StorageError`: Storage backend failures
  - `RetryError`: Max retries exceeded
  - `CircuitBreakerError`: Circuit breaker open

## Roadmap

### Phase 1 (Current) ✅
- [x] Core architecture and interfaces
- [x] Async HTTP client with httpx
- [x] HTML parsing with lxml/BeautifulSoup
- [x] Storage backends (JSON, CSV, SQLite)
- [x] Configuration management
- [x] Basic middleware system
- [x] CLI interface

### Phase 2 (Planned)
- [ ] Browser automation (Playwright integration)
- [ ] Distributed scraping support (Redis queue)
- [ ] Advanced anti-bot handling
- [ ] Real-time monitoring dashboard
- [ ] Job scheduling system
- [ ] REST API for remote control

### Phase 3 (Future)
- [ ] ML-powered selector detection
- [ ] Automatic CAPTCHA solving integration
- [ ] Cloud deployment templates (Docker, Kubernetes)
- [ ] Data quality validation pipeline
- [ ] Web UI for spider management

